sample_extract_protocol_ch1: dounce homogenizers were used to mechanically extract nuclei from cryopreserved mammary tissue. Single nuclei were sorted into reaction buffers (10x genomics) and immediately processed into RNA-seq libraries, single nuclei RNA-seq libraries were generated using 10x Genomics Chromium Single Cell 3' (v3) reagent kits
sample_data_processing: aligment to reference genome "refdata-gex-GRCh38-2020-A" with 10x genomics CellRanger v4.0.0 with modification to retain intronic reads, removal of low quality nuclei and doublets by thresholding number of UMIs (<30.000) and fraction of mitochondrial genes (<2.5%), doublet removal via DoubletFinder (v2.0.2) and manual exclusion of double positive subclusters, integration of all samples into one dataset via Seurat (v.3.2.0) "FindIntegrationAnchors" and "IntegrateData", standard Seurat preprocessi ...
supplementary_files_format_and_content: Seurat Object (.rds) containing raw counts and normalized counts of all samples with metadata and dimensional reduction

sample_extract_protocol_ch1: dounce homogenizers were used to mechanically extract nuclei from cryopreserved mammary tissue. Single nuclei were sorted into reaction buffers (10x genomics) and immediately processed into ATAC-seq libraries, single nuclei ATAC-seq libraries were generated using 10x Genomics Chromium Single Cell ATAC Reagent Kits (v1.1)
sample_data_processing: aligment to reference genome "refdata-cellranger-atac-GRCh38-1.2.0" with 10x genomics CellRanger ATAC v1.2.0, doublet removal in ArchR (v.1.0.0) and batch correction with Harmony (v.1.0), dimensional reduction using iterative-semantic indexing and UMAP, cluster annotation by correlating gene activity scores with clusters identified in RNA-seq data

sample_data_processing: aligment to reference genome "refdata-cellranger-atac-GRCh38-1.2.0" with 10x genomics CellRanger ATAC v1.2.0, doublet removal in ArchR (v.1.0.0) and batch correction with Harmony (v.1.0), dimensional reduction using iterative-semantic indexing and UMAP, cluster annotation by correlating gene activity scores with clusters identified in RNA-seq data
supplementary_files_format_and_content: R object (.rds)
